Not in mealtimes. Because there's too much - on the table, you - you wasn't in - any room for - eight of us and - and - eight of us there to the table, and - and bring anything extra on such as toys and well - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 There'd be no question of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, no, not a bit, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When we ask - if we can leave the table. Manners. Table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes, we was eight and - and - and we had a table large enough for the eight of us. There were three each side of the table, and - and - one each end, so that made the eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well generally, yes, well anyhow we didn't fall out by the chair - who should sit on this chair or - on a form or anything that was going, oh no, no, we was very good for that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You would tend to automatically just sit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, that was right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Now how was meal served, who by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh mother and - well mother generally. Yes, mother would - would - would serve the - or would dish it up and serve it to us and - and you know, all in - well all - all
 in a - a - working man's style like, as it should be for - yes, working people. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you served in any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well the - I suppose that - I suppose in a - a - my father being head of the table see would have his sent 
down as the - elder ones as nearest to him like and so that he would - you would work around that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did mother manage to sit with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, oh well after she served us mother would sit down, but mother was always the last to sit to the table,
 she saw - that we had ours - and comfortably seated and then she would sit and - eat hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Can you remember your younger sister before she was able to come up to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well you see, no, I wasn't much more than eight year old, you don't tak
e much notice as - as - as a young boy do you. No, no. No, no no, I couldn't mind that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mother was an easy person to talk to, did she easily show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - the affection was, if we had a - say - say now a little trivial thing such as
 a headache or toothache and oh mother would try to soothe us, yes. That's what you mean isn't it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was her way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That - yes, yes, yes. Motherly fashion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - as - as we should do. Orderly fashion.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes. Quiet with each other, all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 If another child hurt you did they say you should hit back or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. Everybody stick for theirselves in - in them days didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What kind of people do you think hour parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well sensible - people. Sensible people, I - I should think. You know what I mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - yes, I suppose, yes, yes, yes, all - always try to aim at something a little bit higher I suppose, but then - but then - we never had the education - like they have - today, now -
 I think that all of us was - at school, and - and did very well, I think that - I reached the seventh or ex-seventh standard at school. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they have any views on swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh no, you - my God - huh, mother wouldn't let us swear and father either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 They would object to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh object - yes, ch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 stise us, of course they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. No. No, no interruptions whatsoever. No. No, there was no - two or three yappi
ng the same time, why each one had his say and - singly what they call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 If you did do something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well what would happen was - we should have a good scolding and - and - and if it's anything a bi
t more serious than that we should feel the - weight of their hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You were punished, who would it be by, mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mother. Well - mind - mind, I - I'll allow this, that father was quiet but took - but took him longer - for to get up wh
at they call. He wasn't quick tempered, but mother - was a bit more - a bit more fiery than - than father was in that way, now if mother saw we do anything, now she would rather do it than father. You know what I mean don't ee, 'cos father - if he did do 
it I think would be a bit heavier handed, I think so. So -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How would mother punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - by give us a - like the old people they used to say a lick behind the ear. Or else a - off come your boots and - up to bed, without supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would that happen often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh no, no, no, no, no, no, no, we never - no, we never created anything like that from mother and our father, not - not that I know of, might once in and out, well that's natural, I mean to say that you aren't going to be on a bed
 of roses all the time are you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I suppose if - well I tell you, yes - now - now - up Mr Adma's field, up Troon Moor, he was - a leak running down through the fields, and we use
d to go up there and catch minnows, small fish, well we used to take our boots and stockings off up there and - and - well I suppose that if mother thought we would - come in cold or - or - or have a cold afterwards and she would - tell us of it and be - 
we come in again to dare afterwards well we had a smack, that's what that was and - and - and you know put us in our place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Nothing more serious than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, oh no, no, no, no, oh no, mother wouldn't beat us, not for - the sake of beating of us, no, certainly not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 For your own good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well for our own good, that's right, yes, yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well you know what children are - they'd have a - a good old - well they needed lancin
g some people used to call it, good old lancing or what they call it and then - they would go out and - and cry it off and - and when they come in, well, they'd be better for - for a week or two. Make 'em mind what they call. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would you say that y
ou received the ideas you had about how to behave from both of your parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No - no, no, two of 'em was - about the same - even for that - father tell you to do a thing you would do it, and mother
 tell you to do a thing you would do it, and - as children, young children, we wouldn't go to father if mother said anything. We wouldn't go to mother if father said anything. Their - see each single one was the law. Nowaday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  you get children - oh - mammy,
 my daddy - smacked me or something and then there you are, and then the - wife is up, then the husband, and then there's a - a little - well what shall I say then, a little trouble - oh well just like the - having a teacup - row.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Storm in a teacup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Storm in a teacup, yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When you had a birthday would that be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Birthday. I never seen a birthday cake yet - coming on - in - in the houses, not in they days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Nothing special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No, no, no, no, no. Well we couldn't afford it in they days, times is hard in - in they days. Look - look - I can tell you something now, like I told you just now that I worked - in Grenville, start - seven o'clock in the mornings 'til half past five
, quarter hour croust, and half an hour dinner, now I was only getting five bob a week}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 , there was men underground tram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
ming, yes, and top work for a pound a week. And I can tell you another thing, there was men on the top, men, working for half crown a day 
in they days. A engine driver, I had a chap this way, a fellow from Troon, drive engine, and he only had eighteen shilling a week. That's something isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - as a matter of fact when I got over nine year old I was never home here Christmas Days, I was always out carol singing with the boys, we used to leaver here Troon nine o'clock and get back eight o'clock in the evening, I never had a Christmas dinne
r in this house for years and donkey's years, because - we used to go up Jimmy Rodders and - and them houses, all farmhouses up Black Roack, way to sing, and where we'd go dinner times there was always - how many are you? Six. Oh come in boys, come in, co
m
e in, and there you are, a drop of wine and a - a - hunk of cake we used to call it in they days, and - well - then we'd go - in the afternoon somewhere else like, come on tea time, well you must be hungry children, now come - now come in and - have a pie
ce of - piece of cake or what's going, and sometimes cup of tea then. So there you are, now we used to make our own fun in they days. Now everything fall in your lap now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You didn't do anything together at home on Christmas Day or go to chapel or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, yes, we had to go to chapel, and Sunday school every Sunday, there was no - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 munching}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  of it what they call, no, and my - and we used to go - Sunday school, chapel in the mornings, school in the afternoons and chapel in the
 evening. Unless - unless we were poorly, that's a different matter altogether, wasn't able to go well - and we wasn't drove out to go what they call. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You said you had the organ in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. We did, it was American organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And your sister played it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh my - my father was a lovely tenor singer, and I - I used to sing and - and - Albert, Robert Albert that - that is Cecil's father, the oldest you know boy, he had a lovely v
oice. Now I didn't tell you this morning that - that - he was in the war, first war did I. Cecil's father. To what I said before. Well he was called}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 up - with the other miners in 1916 and he served until the - end of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And he had a good singing voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Who else in the family sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 Well - Annie was a p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
retty good singer. Aye, but Rhoda was organist more or less. She used to - yes, used to sing as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What about you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, I used to sing as well. I had a tenor voice, I was in the chapel choir and - and when I was a boy I sang also in the - choirs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You used to sing together at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 On Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Sundays and Christmas time, yes. Well - quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you join any other musical organisations besides the chapel choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes. Yes, I sang in a - Holman's choir - years ago, when Mr Alder, he - he was the conductor, I sang in the - quarter in Camborne, the Orpheus quarter, and I sang - in Claret's choir after it was formed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was after 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Before 1918 when you were a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes, yes, well - the chapel choir, yes, that's right, the - and going round Christmastime with the - with the - the boys singing - carols. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh used to have a few games you know Christmastime home, in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Any outdoor games, football or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. No, no, I was never in - interested in football or cricket but I used to watch it but never used to play it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes, yes, yes, we had good books in the house in them days. I - Sunday school you know rewards what they call - in the house. Each one had their own, each - member of the house h
ad their own - rewards, I - used to have them from the schools on good Fridays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What sort would they be, story books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well - oh no, no, no history books, more of - well sacred nature I suppose than anything else like, and sometimes we would h
ave a hymn book or - if we was running short of hymn books we used to have hymn books, chapel hymn book or a Sunday school hymn book - a Good Friday present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were there any newspapers in the home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - yes, we used to have the weekly newspapers and all and - we have had - had - Sundays occasionally New of the World and - yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember the names of any of the weekly Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. It was the - the - there's a hotel there now called the - Cornubian. Cornubianor something 
like that it was. That was back in the olden days. Cornubian. Well - and the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Brita}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
n{\*\xmlclose}. Because that been always called that haven't it, West - yes, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Brit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 in{\*\xmlclose}. We used to have that, and we have that still, have the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}West Britain{\*\xmlclose}, and the Packet we'd have now. And the Cornishman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Any magazines in the old days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, mother used to take up Woman's World in them days. I think that was goin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  in they days, yes, Woman's World, and mother used to look forward to it every week, so she could read you know, a bit, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did mother or father ever read aloud to each other or to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No, if - if mother was reading a - a book, she didn't want for any - anybody to be - she couldn't enjoy it if there was anybody else you know talking like or speaking like you know, that's like some people is isn't it, they want it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Read to herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes. Quietness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What, in this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In your own family, when you were a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - no, we was eight of us and - and we kept - eight, well mother and father and the children six of us until - my father died I think first in 1925 I think that was the first one of the - house like. Because what I may say, the family wh
at they called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When did your grandmother die that lived with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - at Porkellis. 1902. 'Cos I was a - a boy then about five. And I mind the - I can mind the - hearse coming. Oh no, it was no hearse at Porkellis, they used to carry them fr
om Porkellis up to Wendron - two miles and a half, and there was singing all the way on the road in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Singing of hymns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, well - the funeral hymns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 From the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 From the house right to the church. Here, and they
 used to drop out in - for taking it again - relays they call it, go so far and then they would - there - there he somebody there walk - waiting to take over like, again the - corpse. Yes, yes, the carrying of the corpse, yes, or coffin, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Who would conduct the service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
That was the - yes, yes, in the church, Wendron church, yes, he was generally the - I - yes, vicar or rector or who - whoever was up there, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would he accompany it all the way from the home or just be at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No, he would be at the church - waiting at the - some gate or other, lunch gate they call it I think. Where they drop them to, when they get there, and then he'd come to a - meet the corpse then, and then they pick - the corpse up again a
nd take it into the church and - and he lead them in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You were very young then but would you remember who attended that sort of funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, I can mind - I can mind people coming up there from Troon. Mrs Hambley - Miss Richards, I don't think s
he was married, and - and Mrs Williams but there was a - Jimmy Williams' mother, now they was all cousins to my mother - they three were, and of course - Mr Hambley - did I say Mrs Hambley, well Mr Hambley was there, and Charlie Williams, that there who w
as Jim's father, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 They were all cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes, yes, they were all in the family and they came from Troon - to my grandmother's funeral, and she was interred at - in - in - in Wendron churchyard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would all your brothers and sisters have at tended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No, well I - well - some would because - I was only five, I knew that I was home with the - people that was - waiting on the table after the funeral - after the funeral people come back like, for tea. I know I was in the house and - neighb
ours like you know come in like and - serve the tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember if they wore mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, they wore mourning in them days, yes. Yes. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Rather more than they do now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - well now I - I - I think - I don't
 think they bother so much now, I think if they've got a - a nice suit now or a nice - set of clothes I mean they were them, I mean to say, the people years ago used to dress up all in black.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 They did - they did in they days t
oo. All black. And if you couldn't afford a suit they'd have a armband put up. Black armband. You've seen it I expect haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 It was quite along way to walk from Porkellis to Wendorn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, well it - it was two mile and a half each way. Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 I - I - I don't get you hardly, I couldn't catch that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you ever taken out by your parents out visiting neighbours, friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, yes, we u
sed to go out to Mrs Roberts - shop - shop, you know, grocers shop and - and my mother and Mrs Robetts were like sisters, we used to go out there as children with my mother and - and - her husband and my father was in the chapel choir together, only Mr Ro
berts, he was a - he was a bass and my father was a tenor and they - quite chummy in the - choir and all together, yes, and they used to have a choir supper in Porkellis in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In the chapel would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - well - it - it - yes, it may
 be in the school because that was separate from the chapel up there. That was the old chapel really, the Sunday school was, and then - I think that there chapel up there is about the same age as this one down here, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 So you would visit your mother's friends sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 With your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes, yes. Well - I had a - I had a - uncle up Porkellis - living, the one that I told you - about - he went to work when he was eight - eight or nine year old, I d
on't know if I told you that, he went to work when he was eight or nine year old, and he drove a horse whim, what they call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In the mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, in - in one of the Wendron mines, now which mine I couldn't tell you, but - you've heard Frank say that. His son.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 A horse whim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would the whim be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Now - as - the whim you see - they never - they - they never had a cage or anything, they might have had a - what do they call it in them days then - a kipple what the
y call a kipple what they call, and the horse you see say if the - shaft was here coming up - like this kibble's coming up see, there the rope - or something attached to the horse, now this horse would walk out this way, for to pull it up, and when its go
ing down - they went a - they bring back the horse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 So that was used to raising and lowering the miners to their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well - well I don't say about the miners 'cos they might have had - had a ladder way for to get down in the shaft theirselve
s, you know, down off the ladder but - but that there was for - for the ore coming up what they call, because - they only had that in very shallow - shafts, just at - at the starting of the mine like, in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was for not very deep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And the boy would be employed driving the horse all day long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes. Yes. And he was only - well we'll say - well he was between eight and nine. And Frank have told us that, that's his son, told us that many times. - Oh by the way, he lived 'til he was ninety-four. Hard work never killed him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember any special outings with father or mother apart from visiting friends or relatives? Being taken on outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Jersey{\*\xmlclose} cars. Troon choir here - the - the - the - the two
 - two chapel choirs here. Couldn't go far in them days because there was only - horses and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Jersey{\*\xmlclose}
 cars. Now - I - I - they'd have a meeting in each chapel and they would come out and say, well where are you going to this year? Oh going home. And Flamouth that was always. If we're going home, that was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Falmouth{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. So - they did go - that chapel choir up there - at the Methodist, went to Newquay one year. We left six o'clock in the morning, got up Newquay twelve, we left six in the evening and got back here - w
hy twelve at night, and they - hitched out their horses on the way up at Zelah for to feed and water them, the same coming home, to feed and water them. At Zelah.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You were in the choir then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, I - I was the alto boy - up - up in the Methodist choir, singing alto. With Annie Jane Williams and - up there in them days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you ever go for any outings with your parents on Bank Holidays, as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, yes, St Ives a bit. By train. By train in them days, yes, and Hayle To
wans, yes, yes, when we got a bit older, the boys, we used to chum up here and we used to go down - Hayle or - you know, or St Ives like, it was cheap in they days, train fares was. But - mother used to take us, and we used to enjoy ourselves as much with
 
the children, mother used to - like take the food with us, up to Uncle Ned's Roack, Chycarne Moor, and we used to go up and have a good old time in the afternoon and evening. Mother'd take food us up there and leave home say about two, get home about - we
ll half past seven or eight o'clock, and we up there roaming around all these big rocks and - well, lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Up on the moors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, Chycarne Moor, Uncle Ned's rock, ever heard of it? That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Not to visit any family or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well shopping to Camborne, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Who would that be with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh mother and father. Used to take us. And - and - of course there was n
o danger in they days because there was no - motor vehicles on the road, there was only horses and carts and cabs and all in they days, it was - isn't like it is now, why - you got to be careful, you got to look where you're going. But, I tell you one thi
n
g that I can mind. George Oliver boot shop - George Oliver, you know where - Hawkins or the television shop is there, who used to have him now, what was his - oh I'll tell you in - Tonkin used to have it didn't it, as you turn round the bus stop there, we
l
l - I can mind George Oliver there - when I was a lad eight or nine years old. And then, after George Oliver turned out from there - he went further down on the other side like, and - fellow called Hockin - Hockin the grocer had it I think, and then - a f
ellow called Ivy took over something didn't he there, and after Ivy of course then comes the television shop and the wireless there, Tonkins. That right?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 So you used to go shopping there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 George Oliver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 s first, yes, he - yes, for our boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Was there anything special about Saturdays, did you spend your Saturday in any different way to other days as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No I don't think so, we used to go out and - and play, like I said to you - just now, we had to go Sunday school and chapel Sundays 
and - and behave ourselves - in Sunday school and chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you all go to Sunday school and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mother and father as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, father sang in the choir see at Troon. And - and - and mother was a - very chapel going woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you have different clothes for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh certainly we did. Yes. Yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes, yes, they wouldn't leave us do anything not - not - what coul
d be done on the weekday - had to be done on the weekday, the Sundays was - a day for - for essential things. Well you've got to eat and drink haven't you on a Sunday. Well they - they are essential things. Well that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Otherwise just attend Sunday school and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Which denomination was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - I - I'm afraid that I've been a bit of a roamer. Now - when I first -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 But as a child which chapel did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, yes, now I - when I come out
 Troon to live first, I - I went to that chapel, United Methodists, and I sang alto up there in the choir, and then I sang tenor - up there afterwards, and I - that was from 19 - well say not - exactly in the choir in 1905, say about 1910, bit older then,
 for singing alto, and then after that I went - I sang on 'til - 1921 or two up there. And then I came down this choir. In the Wesleyan choir.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mother and father both attended the United Methodist as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Earlier on yes, but then they - I don't 
know why, I don't know - I don't know why but they - then they came in - in - down here. But Eddie - Eddie and Willie, they always attended that chapel up - brothers of mine, two brothers, they always went up there, and Eddie, that died, was a - was a sec
retary up there in the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Actually both chapels are very close to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes. Oh yes, yes, yes, yes, well - the - they used to have good old Sankey hymns up there, and - and - and revivals up there when Jolliffe was up there, you can't mind him, Ren Jolliff. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you remember going on any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Mm. Well they never had Sunday school - outings, because they had tea treats didn't them, had the Band of Hope - well the - what do you call it, it was a - we 
always had our tea treats here, in each - chapel, on Midsummer Day, and - and two bands, one for each Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would take place then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - the children - would walk - round the village, and make the - figure eight in the Square, com
e up their - schools, each one, and they had a - had buns - and a mug of tea, and then - over to the f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
ir field, or - we used to say - just a day or two before Christmas - why the fair, some used to say, oh yes, the Shaws are come. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they have any games at the Sunday school treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, yes. Old Jolly Miller and Duggin Rind and - and Kidsing Ring. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was quite a highlight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, oh yes, that was a highlight in - in the evenings, and - and - and that would go on 't
il - ten or eleven o'clock in the field there, we used to go out in - in Mr Hampton's field in they days, and the other chapel - used to go in the - in the Brewery field. That was right wasn't it, the two - fields. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That's behind the pub, the Brewery field?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes. And - and the buns - in them days was - was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 
- was baked in Troon, Williams'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  the bakers, and they were sixteen ounce in they days, pound bun. Now I don't think they're more than about six ounces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were there any other social activities that you can remember organised by the chapel that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well, yes, in - in the Band of Hope. And - children - of the Sunday schools - each one like in turn would give a - a little concert like, a children would and - I can min
d up the - well we used to call it the top chapel, United Methodist - they used to have - why a - every Good Friday had a pageant, and that was a - a big thing up there. A pageant. That right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Sort of religious play, drama?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, used to have 
- yes, yes, why - I forget the name was in it now, the names. Mr Stee Angove was in it, Arthur Roberts. Mrs Richards. May Roberts that - that was.
