 - years ago, Doctor Crippen was all the go in them days at the fair and they used to be inside a - like a door like with a hole in the door and they used to throw the ball so that they - hit him, the door would open and he would gr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 adua}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060953\charrsid3099254 ly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
 come down - in front, so we could see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What form of transport did the fair travel with in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh when I come out to Troon to live first in 1905 - there were all horses, some - some used to have so many horses to their - little fairs - oh - a dozen t
o eighteen horses for different wagons and stalls and all that was in the wagon packed away, yes and not only that but there used to be - three or four different - three or four different way - lot of people with the fair, one was the Jones's and - I can 
-
 mind when we come out Troon here first I think it was Sophie Hancock's show that - fair that used to come to Troon, and other fairs like besides and - and then there was a - a game called hoop-la, that was all the go in them days, hoop-la. You used to th
row a hoop over the article that was on the stall like, and if it cleared it was all right and he went down over the article, but - and if he did you had a prize, but - it was hard to get.
