\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - 
I don't think there was any - recreation ground in Troon when I came out Troon to live first, because we used to go up - in the fields, up Chycarne Moor, what they call and - Chycarne, and in the fields around Chycarne Moor to play. I think that Troon rec
r
eation ground - was - was open - a short while after the first war I think it was, and - and Pendarves owned the ground then, Squire Pendarves. Yes. And the - recreation - and the cricket ground as well, he - he owned in them days. That's the Troon cricke
t ground that is now.
