\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You told me that father was in hospital for three weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What difference did it make to the family if father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, I - by the way I'l
l answer this question first with his hand, I couldn't think of it just now, he had a lupus cut out of his hand. And - he went to the - Helston doctor's, and they tended him, but - his hand didn't get any better. Then he went to an old quack what they cal
l
 in them days, and - I think that made it worse. So when he came out - when he's out in Grenville he seen some men and he said, well look - they said, look Robert, why don't you go down Camborne and see Doctor Tonkin, oh he was a man in they day, doctor T
o
nkin, well - father went in surgery and seen Doctor Tonkin and show him his hand, Doctor Tonkin said, who been meddling with your hand? Well - this quack he said, well he said, well - I don't know, he said, I've tried everything and - he don't seem to be 
g
etting any better doctor. No, he said, he said, Robert you must go hospital - with your hand. And he said, I - I'll make arrangements for you, we was at Porkellis in they days mind, and - well - in hospital. Mother could only go up hospital - once a week,
 Fridays, in - in the bus from Porkellis, and the only owner of the bus was called Opie. Mr Opie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Which hospital was that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In the Miners Hospital, what they called in them day. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In Redruth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, Redruth hospital, w
ell mother went up - the Friday, or the second Friday, I don't know which it was now, and she went to the hospital and enquired for - her husband like you know, his name and all, and - she - mother expected to see him in the ground sitting on the seat. Ju
s
t his hand. So - no - he was - he was - in the bed. He was in hospital three weeks. Mother - mother didn't - expect for him to be in the bed with his hand, but then it must be something to do with the - with something in - in the body - yes, must have bee
n.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Who was the quack then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh I don't know who - somebody - somebody from out around Helston way somewhere, not in the town it wasn't, somebody out around -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would he do, set up as having some knowledge of medicine that people would go to him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well they used to go to these sort of people - if - if you had a - if you had warts on your hands in they days or anywhere, or ring worms or - they used to - yes, used to charm what they call in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 It looked like a wart and that was why father thought -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well it looked - well, it was very - it was very painful, or - or he could have been - thinking it might have been a little cyst or something. It could have been. But - he was in hospital for - for three weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did mother manage about money then, did she get paid from the mine or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh I couldn't you that, no, no, I couldn't tell you, no, I was a bit - that - look now look I wasn't no more than a little lad, I - in fact I can't mind my mother up there - hospital. Now, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 They told you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, that's right, yes, she told me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you ever get help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you recall anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, I can mi
nd - I can mind women here, Troon - that they - if their husband was - sick or wasn't - and never worked for a long time or if their husbands was killed or anything they had to - had to trust every Mon - every Monday morning - I - for the parish wagon com
e
 up - half - half crown a week and loaf of bread, for the wife - for the wife - or the woman and the children, and on top of that if she went out to work she had to work - hard in them days - scrub the - do all the washing and after the washing - had to s
crub the floors, for a shilling a day. It's not like that today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Where would this parish cart have come to in your village then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh right up through - any - anyone that needed it would come up, he - he would call to the houses that - yes, yes, he
 had the names of the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And he call?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 At the door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 They didn't have to queue up at any special place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh no, no, no, no, no, no, he would call at the houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you know how he would treat the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well you see - I
 don't think - well they - the men might have come - himself, now what do you call that man in them days? A - a relieving officer, that's right, relieving officer, and a driver, they were two, the driver and him would come, and - and the women - who - who
 - or whoever come out to 'em, may have been the children come out but it's the same thing, they had half a crown, and - and a loaf of bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I - I suppose - if they knew who was the - who was in authority over this I suppose they would go - and air their grievance what they call. Like they would today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you remember anyone being made to leave the district by people sort of drumming them out the town or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No, I can mind a man when I was a very - when I come out Troon just after I come out Troon to live first, over Lady Road there was a fellow - he didn't pay the rent from his hous
e - and evicted, and I can mind them taking the furniture out and putting - putting the furniture opposite this house, on the - against the edge the other side. I can mind that when I was a little boy, and that was where - this live now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You don't know what happened to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well no, no, no, I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You just saw that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 I just saw that, yes, that' was all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well I lived up Porkellis and I started school when I was five year old
, and I - went to Halwin school, which is - from a mile to a mile and a quarter each way - and I would leave home half past eight in the mornings and get home four o'clock in the afternoons, and carry me dinner with me - and - dinnertime I wo}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 ld come out, 
and - there was an old mine called - Medlyn Moor, and there was a shoot of water there, and we - I used to take my little bit of food, and - and go down to the shoot and have a drink out the shoot, cold water. Now - there was milk in school in them days, 
there was no hot meals in them days, neither transport. So - I left school - when I was eight year old at the - at - I went through the infants school. Past the infants.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You took your own lunch, would they give you anything to drink in the school, any hot drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Not that I know of, I never had any hot tea up there, because - in them days - well they was like other schools was - there was a stove in the centre of the - of the room, classrooms, with the chimney going up through the roof, straight c
himney. I forget the name of the stove now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 American stoves did they call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well there's a ring on top that you - pulled down the coal and you rake out the ashes from in the bottom like. Yes, something like that it was called, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You didn't have any teaching from your parents or anybody before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - well no, why the - why the - the parents - they wasn't very educated theirselves so therefore they couldn't pass on the - on this - on the reading or - writing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 This school at Halwin, this was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - that was the county council school that was like they are today because - that - we all had to go to school in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And you walked to school, a mile and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Each way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long would it have taken you from home to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I suppose - you couldn't - you couldn't walk - to school much - much under - of course we had to go up school - get in school by nine o'clock, so - I suppose that we - tried to be
 in good time, get to school between and ten and - ten and four - ten or five to nine, something like that, and we leave school in the infants in they days - half - half past three. So I used to get home about - nearly four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 About half an hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Each - each way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Who would go with you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh well - the children from Porkellis and - and you know - I mean brothers and sisters - and my brother - Albert - he left school - Halwin school before he came out - out Troon to live, 
because he was fourteen before he come out Troon and - he walked from - up Porkellis out Grenville, as a little boy, fourteen, five mile each way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 He didn't ride on the donkey shay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - oh no, my father was underground and he was up surface working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes. And there were - a good many - men - that used to - used to work - out in Grenwille from up Porkellis, and - lads as well, and they used to - used to team up like - they - and maybe three or four from up there were in
 the mine the same time and used to come - well you know, company like for each other, and winter mornings - Albert had to start seven o'clock in the mornings. And - he - he'd leave home about - about quarter to - quarter to six, of course he had to walk 
five mile you know, it - it took him an hour and a quarter, each way. Leave work at half past five and get home nearly - seven o'clock in the evening. A long day for a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You'd take your food to school, where would you eat it? In school classrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well we couldn't eat 'em in - the classroom - if - if - if there's rain - eat it in the lobby what they call where we hang up our - hat and coat to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Where did the teachers eat theirs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - oh I suppose they used to eat theirs in school I suppose, yes, I expect so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would you have taken to school to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - there's what they do call - what they call in the olden days - a heavy Hoggan. A pasty. Change. And egg sandwiches. That's what we used to carry to school in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Heav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 y hogg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
an was a sort of heavy cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. No, heavy cake, with a - had figs in it. Figgy hoggan some call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What did you think of school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well in them days I - I wasn't old enough to - realize I don't suppose because - i
n the infants school you don't - think much, but when I come out here Troon school I went to - standard - one first and then I - worked my way up into - until the seventh or ex-seventh - seventh standard, at top of the class or top of the class nearly so,
 don't suppose I was too bad a scholar in they days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - yes, I got on all right at the school all my time, mind I don't know that ever I've never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 munched}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  what they call. Stay away. No, I never stayed away from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 At Porkellis f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 rst and then at Troon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well the - the teachers - in the infants school well, they're not too - hard on the children because they're young, but - the - Master James was - was a nice fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Where was he, at Porkellis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well he - he lived in Halwin in the school house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 He was the headmaster at Halwin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, he was the headmaster. Mm. Yes. I - liked Master Moreshead here - here at Troon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - up - when - when I came to Troon you see it was a different - thing all - oh well I was older you see and when you get from the infants up to - or in the standards then see, you're always rising, y
ou're always learning a bit more every year aren't you, you know, I mean to say you've got a little bit more - well a little bit higher education every class you go up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What about manners, did they emphasise that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, yes, they emphasise - emphasise manners, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes, yes, you had to be tidy going to school, you - of course - Troon school they had their - wash ups and all in the lobby up here, so - and soap you could wash your hands and all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they have that at Porkellis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, I couldn't say for the infants, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Punctuality, did they emphasise that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Nine o'clock - they - had a bell - up Troon school in them - in them days to ring. But - latterly - I haven't heard that for y
ears and years. So when we come out to Troon first it was always a - a bell in the school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 ring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they emphasise anything about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - well no I don't think that you - you know, I mean to say that you - I don't know if y
ou was - I - or they didn't want for ee to be - too old fashioned what they call, but if - if you was in the - well, you know, were decent like in speaking it's all right. Decent way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen? How would they punish the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well they would give ee - they would give ee - a good telling off, they - they would call you out in - in front of the class like, and that would make you look a bit small. And - you know. But - I can mind - the b
oys up there - years - say the elder boys up there, I can mind them - sometimes that the master had to cane them, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What sort of offences would they be caned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - I don't know, I - I'm sure - well I suppose they - well I - I wasn
't - in their class, not up - in the class like that but - I knew they were caned. But not very often, you had to do something - drastically - wrong or bad for - for a teacher or master to cane you in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would girls get the same punishment as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Now in Troon school you see - the three separate compartments, there's the infants school, there was a girls school, and the boys school and - and there wasn't a mixed school with the - with the boys and girls, and there were - a dividing wall 
in them times, so the girls - had their ground, and boys had - their ground - why - for a playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - they wanted to know - when I came home from school - was I a good boy at school an
d done what I was told like other - other parents would ask. I said yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
No. No. No, if - if I - had the cane - there's no good for me to go home and tell mother and father that, because they knew Mr Harvey and th
ey knew Mr Morsehead. Nowadays - if that happen - why the - parents are up after the teachers, but not in - in them days like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, if they's on the road, Master Moreshead like I said if I he come on you he'd h
ave a chat with father and mother or - Mr Harvey, and Mr Harvey was a - active man up to the chapel. Up United Methodist. He was a - Sunday school teacher and I believe that he was something - well he must have been on the trustees or something in the cha
pel, I know he was a - well a big figure at what we call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Was Mr Moreshaed a chapel person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, church. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, I - I think the - I think he took the - you know, class - as a whole like you know, on the whole what you call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did the other children come from similar types of homes to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you recall if there were any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, not that I kn
ow of. No, I - if - if they was willing or do - or done what they was told, they - they would be the same as the other children, they could - be - in the class and - have the same teaching or - or - or the same - things that was going that the others had.
 I - I don't think there's any - one like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. Not in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you go on to any other school after leaving Troon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh no, no. I went to work, in Grenville, I left school October 1
911, I went - in Grenville - on the surface what they called, in ten yard and other jobs and in the mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Fourteen, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would you have stayed longer at school if you'd had the opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well I - I don't think there was any - any longer - I think that was the - leaving age, fourteen was in them days. Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you attend any par}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 t-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 time education afterwards at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, none at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Do you have any regrets about your schooling or education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I don't know - I don't know that I - I look back and - I'm sorry - of anything I mean to say that - I got on all - all right through life and - I - I'm living still and - and a very good age, turned seventy-five so - not much to grumble about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You benefitted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes, well - everybody should because you - you're - you're supposed to - I mean - do your own business to read and write and if you can't do that - nowaday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  - well you're looked upon as a - well a - a little retarded shall I say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 While you were at school did you have any part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. No, I had not - regular at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Just sometimes taking the cobbling job for Mr Bastion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, well that was about - maybe once a week or once a fortnight or once a month and may have tuppence or three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 pence just like that, you know, in them days why three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 pence in - in they days was as good as - well two shilling now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 I should like to ask you about your first full time job down at the mine, what was the very first job that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 In the tin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 yard. Under - Mr Jack Shearman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would that be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - in the pack
ing shed - first, used to pack - the tin in a kieve, and until - until it was - until it was hard so they could take it up, and they had to shovel that out then. And then that went on the frame.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What's a kieve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 A kieve is a big - vat, but don't
 put that down, it's a wood thing with lots of - hoops on it, and he's about - three foot in diameter and as high as this table. And - and we had to - had to pack - had to pack that with a barrow, with an iron bar and then from there I went out then in th
e - yard to work - in - on the frame, round frames, and - and then - on the bu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 dles, afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That's separating the tin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh no, well the - that's all in the - in the work like you know, from the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 frames you would go - on the bun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 dles. From there
 - you go in the packing shed - where it had to be packed. And from there he would go in different kieves, what they call, until he come to the mixing kieve what they call, and then that was the tin that used to used to go in the tin house that did, and s
ample and sack - for - for the market. The smelting works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Part of the process of dividing the ore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes. Well - the frames and all you see - the good - the - the tin - was always on top, but the sand - would always - run down to the tailings sort of what they call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Dividing the tin from the sand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, that's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, I - I went - from the school and - and asked for the job - round the - boss is called - Reynolds I th
ink in they days, I went to him and I said - I want a job. He asked me my name, I told him and - he said - I think that they can do with a - a boy - up in the tin yard. I said, all right. He said, when can you start? I said, well I - I've left school, sta
rt Monday. He said all right. So I went on. From there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You said you worked from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Seven o'clock in the morning 'til half past five in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 With two breaks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Croust and dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, nine 'til quarter past nine croust.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. Not in the mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, half day Saturdays. Yes, leave at one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, Good Friday. And Bank Holiday. And - Christmas Day, but we had to work - next day 'til dinnertime, Boxing Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What were you paid for your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - five bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well all the boys had that in they days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Gave her all. Had to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What would it be spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - on - on - on the general household commodities, such as food and - and - lighting and - rent, rates, all these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What about pocket money, mother would give back some for pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, trifle pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well in - in them days you had to work hard. Never had much time for
 to - for to chat much or nothing because you had your work to do in - in them days you know, why - it was hard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
graft in the mines wasn't it, because - the tin stuff is heavy for to - for a shovel all day long you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How did you feel about your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I don't know that I - I don't that is - either one, I mean to say the - the - it was a job and you had to work somewhere and you - and - well I made the best of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long were you occupied in this particular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I was on different jobs - on - on the top what they call, I went over to the - to the Count House then, for to help in the Count House and - clean the knives and forks and bring in the coa
l and there was a two women there, and - charged their lamps up for underground, carbide lamps the bosses had. Carbide lamps with a hand - handle to them and take - carry them in their hand, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 So that was general duties, anything that wanted doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - yes, fetch the water - because they had a - a barrel outside, a water ba}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14381211\charrsid3099254 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 rel outside and - used to carry - well - you'd get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 pail}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  and pull up that and then take it into the - in - into the kitchen where they wanted it to and - and if they wanted more I'd go out fetch more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long in all were you working on the surface then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - oh three or four year I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And then after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Underground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 So that would be when you were about seventeen or eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Y
es, I - I was down with father - then tributing, and that was hard work in they days I tell you because - there were no machines in the mines - or - not many machines shall I say, 'cos - it was all hand labour in they days, hammer and drill, and - the mac
hines that was in the mines was used for driving ends what they call, the levels, you know, drive them in further, and - and - raising, raising. And they were all Holman's machines in they days. They were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
hundredweight machines what they call and th
ey were rigged up on a bar, and you had to put in a piece of wood - against the - hanging wall, and the foot wall, to keep - and - and then they used to - well, kind of - with threads on it - screw on it you see, so if would tighten up as - so it shouldn'
t fall.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 To shore up the workings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes, yes, when it was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long did you work underground then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, until it - until Grenville knocked. August 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What jobs have you done since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What was the first one after you left Grenville?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Left - I left in Grenville. I was on a quarry - I worked in a quarry should have said, up Black Rock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 A stone quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Elvan quarry, yes, stone, elvan yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long were you up there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - oh a good while. Don't know exactly now. And then from there - I went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would it be a couple of years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well no I wouldn't say it's hardly that, may have been about - from twelve to eighteen months or something like that I should think.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That would be about 1920 to 22?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mm. Yes, yes. Well - then - after that - I went to - let's see now, where's to after 1921.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What were you doing at the stone quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, quarry, I - oh yes, general, sometimes - and sometimes I was in the 
quarry, and the other times, I - I - I was on the - you know crusher - crushing the stone for metal on the road what they call that, a crusher, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 For making roads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Quite right, yes, and then I worked on the council - for - a while. A
nd then the dole come. Hard times come. I was on the dole several times.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How long were you on the council then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well I - I - I was up - Ladock working - I lodged in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Truro
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} then, when I was on the - on the council - that time. I was under the country council - then, up - up Ladock, on the roads and in the quarry up there working, oh about - I should think about nine months. Up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was similar work to the stone quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, oh yes. Yes. That's right. And then - yes, and then I went down Falmouth Docks to work - two innings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Any idea when roughly that would have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - 192 - 1925 I suppose, somewhere round that time, it was. I did the two innings. 1925 and 26.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 A couple of years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Mm. Well - a bit of singing in between they jobs, of course - it didn't carry on not - right on like job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Just casual jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Then after 1926?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, I - I worked over to the Bartles Foun - not Bartles Foundry, I was over there when the w
ar was on, now what job did I have then? After 19 - 1926. Oh I was on Camborne Council again - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was sort of roadman was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, yes, making roads - from Camborne - down to - oh - Roscroggan. Then there's other 
singing between these see. See, I - I - I done all that - I don't know that I've got the dates exactly right, it may be longer periods than that because - because - well singing you - you couldn't have a job here for - sometimes I'd sing for up eighteen m
onths or two years. Well you see - well they dates wouldn't correspond with all that lot see. So - well all as I can say is I've had different jobs, after the mine knock that's all. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you in any job for any length of time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes, yes. Yes. I down factory for seventeen years. ICI.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You can remember that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh, that was the period - that was a period before he closed down, 1961. I went down in - 19 - oh what - 1944 or five, just like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Just at the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Yes, yes. And before then - I was over - over Bartles Foundry work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 That was during the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 During the war, yes. And - Holy - Holywell Camp just before the war, and - and after the - and while the war was on for a short ti
me, say - might have went over the - round the Christmas like and I finished the - end of March or - or April, up Holywell Camp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What sort of camp was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Army camp. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What were you doing at the army camp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well, I - well digging trenches for - for them - or - or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Building the camp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, oh yes, building the camp for soldiers, yes. Yes. Well it wasn't no air station, it was a camp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Army camp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Bartles Foundry the whole of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, no, no, no, not the whole of the - the whole of the war, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 It - it may have been about four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would you have preferred another type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Now - well I - I was over Bartles - a foundry as I was saying, I was on the cutting machi
ne, and - and I was cutting for the government on different jobs, sometimes for the navy, sometimes for the air}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
force, and - and - and the army - I was on the cutting machine, it - it consisted of - of a cylinder of oxygen - and gas, household gas, mixed, and that was the - why the - what I had to burn with, for the job.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What were you cutting then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I - I was cutting - out steel for - ack - ack guns for the sights. And - then I was cutting for the - admiralty, I don't know exactly what it is for but - I was informed - as I was doing the job, it was for the Admiralty, the air}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 force and the army, the jobs that I was cutting for, it was all for the government.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You did that most of the time you were at Bartles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes, yes, I was very skilled, all the time I was - at Bartles Foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 When you worked at ICI those seventeen years could you tell me what sort of work you did there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, I - I was taken on for the engineering shop for to help the - help, you know, fitter and - an
d if I was wanted out in the rooms for oiling and greasing, I - I used to do that, or - on the belts, or anything in general, I - that I was asked to do - in the engineer - engineering shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well I don't know, I didn't think - anything about that much because - I was in jobs and - I was out of jobs like other people and - what other jobs that I did well - I didn't mind doing, I - I know I had to work and - and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you serve an apprenticeship or any training period for any of the jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, none at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Not for the one at Bartles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh - no, no, I - I had a - a fellow - when I started on the - on the cutting machine, that was a new thing and - he came down for 
a couple of day, and he showed me - how to work it, well you know, demonstrated what they call to me and after two days he said, well, he said, OK, he said, you can do the job all right. So he left. I think he was from a firm up the country somewhere. Thi
s fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes. Oh General Workers - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
, the General Workers, what do you call it - General Workers and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 General and Municipal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes - well - don't matter - General Workers union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - years ago - I did attend the - the union meetings. It - if was always held at Camborne, it was - quite a way to go, after you come home from - from work but I did attend some meetings. Of the union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - you - you had your job to do, and - and - and if the - if the boss like came up with a job that you wanted to be done, you - he'd tell you what you must do and of course - w
hich we done it, we carried on with the job that was the - all that I think that we - I think that I've got on all right wherever I've worked with the - with the bosses. I didn't have any trouble. I was never sacked as you might say for - for not doing th
e right thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you feel that there were any divisions among the workers themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Well - no, I don't think so, even if they were trades - men what they call, and they wanted a bit of a hand like or a bit of help you would - you would help t
hem and - he was no - well - the high and mighty over it at all, used to go on quietly with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Once you were in full time work after you left school did that change your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. Because - because mining - then was the - well - only occupation really, there was a foundry in Camborne, Holman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
s foundry but - but - in Troon and - well - and in Camborne as well go for that - there was nearly all miners, underground and surface miners, that was the - most occupation that was going - in the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did starting full time work change your relationships with your parents or brothers and sisters in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you spend your Sundays any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well in the normal way. I - Sundays we
 used to go - Sunday school and chapel and go out for a - a walk, but never work on a Sunday, in - in earlier days at all, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you yourself take any interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - no, not a lot, not when I was young I didn't. I didn't unti
l I got at - well - middle age I suppose, something like that. I used to vote though. But - when I was - eligible to vote I voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you have any views on politics then, now how you voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 1918 would be your first election wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 1918 - yes, well - Mr Aclad was here at the time, and the Liberal, and I used to - I used to vote - Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Why did you support that particular political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well because my mother and father were - were always you know Liberals a
nd I followed suit I suppose and - I thought they - I thought they were doing the right thing and - I did that as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for any particular party? From your employers or anyone like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh no. No, they never said anything, never - asked us who - who was we going to vote for nor nothing, that was up to us, who we voted for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Were you a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well, I can't say that I - I followed up any meetings or anything 
- but the electioneering when it came on as I said I was a Liberal, because the - Labour - wasn't in the district in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Have you always voted Liberal since that first election or have you changed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - I - well I have changed, yes, I - I - I was a Liberal for years and then I went to Labour and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And it just amounted to voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You took no active part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You told me how you spent your spare time as a youngster, did that alter all once 
you went to work? Your main interest then was in choir work, did it continue that way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes. And still am interested - in choirs now, I - I go to - mostly all the concerts and - and - and I do sing with the Toc H - up Troon every Christmas, for the - to - help the old age and - and the sick and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time, once you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - no, I don't think so, I used to go out in - in - in Troon like I do now in the village and we used to 
have bit chat when I was young, and I still have a chat with the - if there's anybody - out Troon that we can have a chat with, why - I don't - I don't think that made any difference - because I was working - more than it do now. I was always on the socia
ble side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 And you continued your interest in the institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh yes - me mates and that - well, quite often - used to come in and - of course if I wasn't - if I wasn't ready to go out - if I wasn
't tidy they used to call it in the olden days, well I would say, well come in and sit down and wait and - I shant be long and - and of we'd go somewhere for a walk or - cycle, or anything like that, good old cycle ride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Your parents met your friends of course, they came to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did your parents expect to know where you were if you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well - no, I don't think so, not after I was fourteen because - I should have been old enough to look after myself and - and came in th
e time that I ought to come in for - for next day to work, because we - we had - had to have our rest you know, because in the mines was - hard work in them days, for boys. So we - had to take our rest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you have to be home by a certain time, did your parents say you should be or did they just leave it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh - well - I would - yes, yes, well when I was out and - and - come around about nine or half past nine - I - I used to make my way home where I was and - and get - I got home then and 
had bit of supper and - bit of chat, well time to go to bed and - of course I had to be out early in the mornings you know, for work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 What about Saturdays, did you do anything special on those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well I - I had to work Saturdays - in the mines until dinnertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Then afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh, in the afternoons, well - well I used to go - cricket matches in the summer a lot, and then - well tea treats when there was any tea treats about in the summer of a Saturday afternoon I - well there's a 
- a lot of tea treats in them days, where nowaday, they put them to the seaside and - well beach what they call. The old time - the old time looks to me of - died out now for tea treats, and they rather have a bit of ride than they would have a nice littl
e bit of fun in the field.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 If you did go out in the evening where would you normally go to in the village or around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Well that all depends - if it's winter or summer, it it is winter we had to go in - go in out the rain and cold, we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 'd go in the institute and have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
 a game of cards and billiards and - bit chat and - but if the summer time we would - we would go out around the outskirts of Troon and - for a nice a walk or - or like I said just now, have - have a nice bike ride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did you ever go swimming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 No. No. No. Afraid I should sink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Would you go for walks with a girl sometimes? Or take them home from choir practice perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 The choir - practice started a - bit and - then we go and - and come out, well on the way out we used to
 have bit of chat and - well may see one or two home, bit shiner sometimes that's all, there - there's nothing in it more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Bit of shiner, that's friendly for a short while? Going back to your early youth when you used to burn furze in the op
en fireplace, would that be one of your little jobs as a child to gather it in, or who would get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 How would they get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 All of us, I mean father - and - and the boys would go off together sometimes and sometimes the boys woul
d do it on their own, we had what they call a - a hook in them days and now I call it a - what they call it in - what is it, a thistle or something, hammer and thistle, to cut it. Well I think the - I think the correct name of a hook is a thistle or somet
h
ing like that, anyhow, it was - used for cutting down the wood, furze sticks, and we used to take them home, and - well make a little wick of them, and when we - mind this was in - in the summer when they were dry or in the autumn like when they were dry,
 
and then - we used to thatch them with the rushes what - that grows - in - in the moors, in the marsh the rushes used to grow, and - and we used to - roof them what they called, to keep them dry. And then when we wanted the - wanted them in the winter, we
 used to go out and - and - and take them from this little rick. Yes, and burn them in the brandis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 , in the open chimney.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Can you think of anything more you used to do of an evening as a young man or any other places you used to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Go in Cambor
ne, and - I used to ride in the tram cars. Mind, the tram cars came in Camborne first - in 1903 and they ran from Camborne in Redruth, about three mile each way, and the fare was only tuppence each way then in old money, and it was - it - it was a big day
 in Redruth you know, on Whit Mondays. Oh a big fair in there, Anaton and Rowlands and thousands - of people, you - you had a hard job to get on the tram - to go in to the f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
