\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254  eleven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7569021\charrsid3099254  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
pence each way now, new pence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 You would use the tram cars when you had time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh well - oh yes, yes, we used to go in Redruth if there was anything doing leaving out the fair or - if there's a nice concert, band concert out in - in the park in Redruth, we used 
to go in there, and we used to go in there - a bit of a Saturday evening like after tea if it is nice weather, and we always used to get on top in the tram, one of the open deck old - and we could look for miles - on the road, see all the - hills and the 
valleys and they chimney stacks and the mines and - oh - lovely, lovely that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Can you remember anything that happened in the fair at Redruth on Whit Mondays before 1918? Was it anything like the fair that came to Troon or was it bigger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Oh ye
s, that was a big concern - in Redruth. Why - they used to call it in the Fair Medda, and that was - jam full of people - well - well rubbing - shoul - or elbow to elbow in there, you couldn't pass in - into the - not for the people, and the fair - cor - 
I
 don't know how many sets of horses is in there and - well, and condoles there was in them days there was, and - side shows by the galore. Shooting galleries - oh, I don't know what was all in it. Helter skelter in - in they days was the thing. They used 
to take a mat - and - and go up well it is like a tower, and they used to come down - with their mat under their backside or supposed to be, but they used - used to lose the mat quite often and slide out on the ground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6423890 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 Did they have any boxing or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409093 WF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10693638\charrsid3099254 
Oh yes, yes, yes. They had their - there were two or three in boot what they call and these men would be out - outside and the - and the boss what they call used to be saying well, who'll challenge - who - who'll - challenge this one h
ere and - and then they - oh he - he was so and so also and so and so, he would challenge you for so many rounds, and if you knock out the man that - you go to challenge, you'd have so much money, so - all the people used to throng in the tents - to see t
he boxing - exhibition going on. Lovely, lovely. Good old days they were.
\par 
